  "text": "The regulatory role(s) of cytokinins during secondary woody growth has been known [CITATION_1] . However, it was only recently demonstrated that modification of cytokinin biosynthesis can have a positive effect on secondary woody growth [CITATION_2] . Transgenic poplars transformed with the Arabidopsis AtIPT7 (key cytokinin biosynthetic gene) driven by a xylem-specific promoter, showed significant (nearly 2-fold) increases in secondary growth and no negative pleiotropic effects [CITATION_3] (Figure 2A ).",
